   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Follow this procedure to clear plugs from the batch system:</p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <note id="note_lp4_r1x_rcc" class="- topic/note ">
               <table id="table_ovl_s1x_rcc" class="- topic/table ">
                  <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">
                                 <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">PPE Required</b>: Respirator or PAPR.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">Inhalation hazard.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">Silica hazard.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">Pinch hazard.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Tools Required</b>: Rubber mallet, pry bar.</note>
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To clear clogs from the day bin, strike the outside of the bin using a rubber
               mallet.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Open the inspection door to remove hard batch that might be blocking the
                     opening of the hopper. </li>
               </ul>
               <note type="note" id="note_xfk_jbx_rcc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Metallic hammers can damage equipment and cause more frequent plugging.</p>
               </note>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_lrs_xwv_rcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image1.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_syz_s41_tcc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <note id="note_h1f_1xv_rcc" class="- topic/note ">
               <table id="table_ucv_1xv_rcc" class="- topic/table ">
                  <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">
                                 <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">PPE Required:</b> Respirator or PAPR.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">
                                 <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">LO/TO</b>
                              </p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">Silica hazard.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </note>
            <note type="note" id="note_hly_lfx_rcc" class="- topic/note "> Bindicators are located at the head and tail of
               the bucket elevator and mixed batch conveyor.</note>
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If a system clog is detected near a Bindicator:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">LO/TO</b> the clogged equipment </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Remove the access panels, and clear any clogs.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Determine the cause of the clog, and take the necessary corrective
                     actions.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Replace access panels, and reset the system.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Remove the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">LO/TO.</b>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Reset the system as described in BAT-ET-101B Resetting the Batch System After
                     an E-Stop or Fault.  </li>
               </ul>
               <note type="note" id="note_hp3_y2x_rcc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">The access panels weigh approximately 6.8 kg (15 lb)</p>
               </note>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <note id="note_pm1_lxv_rcc" class="- topic/note ">
               <table id="table_sxd_mxv_rcc" class="- topic/table ">
                  <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">Slip hazard.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </note>
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">One common cause of clogs is excessive batch moisture.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">The indicator on the water meter should only turn when the mixer is
                     running.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">If the indicator is turning when the mixer is not running, the automatic valve
                     is malfunctioning.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">If water is running when the mixer is off, close the manual valves until
                     repairs can be made.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Clean up any spilled water. </li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_m4x_yfx_rcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image3.jpg"
                            id="image_sq2_1p1_tcc"
                            placement="break"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <note id="note_bff_qxv_rcc" class="- topic/note ">
               <table id="table_ryh_rxv_rcc" class="- topic/table ">
                  <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                     <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">
                                 <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">PPE Required</b>: Respirator or PAPR.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">Dust hazard.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">Toxic materials.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">Pinch hazard.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row class="- topic/row ">
                           <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                           <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                              <p class="- topic/p ">Fall hazard. Utilize 3 points of contact on ladders. </p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Tools Required</b>: Rubber mallet, pry bar.</note>
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "/>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">LO/TO</b> the charger when breaking up the buildup from the inside of the
                     hopper with a pry bar.</p>
                  <ul id="ul_q1r_bq1_tcc" class="- topic/ul ">
                     <li class="- topic/li ">The charger can remain running while tapping on the outside of the
                        hopper.</li>
                  </ul>
               </note>
               <p class="- topic/p ">To clear clogs from the surge hopper, strike the outside of the bin using a rubber
                  mallet.</p>
               <ul id="ul_shj_zhx_rcc" class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Use a pry bar to break up clogs from the top of the hopper.</li>
               </ul>
               <note id="note_mty_jc4_vcc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Do not damage nearby instruments, such as the moisture analyzer.</p>
               </note>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_wnq_s3x_rcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_ilj_jq1_tcc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_q4t_lq1_tcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image5.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_lj3_mq1_tcc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If the surge hopper needs to be unclogged from the bottom:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul id="ul_g2t_tjx_rcc" class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Inform the forming operator about the situation.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Stop charging.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Complete steps 5.2 through 5.9</li>
               </ul>
            </info>
            <substeps id="substeps_fgt_tjx_rcc" class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> At the Melter workstation, go to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Melter JF </b>screen and click the
                        <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Overview</uicontrol> tab.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ul id="ul_hqx_mlx_rcc" class="- topic/ul ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Click the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Charger Profile</uicontrol> button, and check the
                              <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Suppress</b> checkbox.</li>
                     </ul>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_xcl_31w_rcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image6.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_x1x_qq1_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">At the Zippe Integration touch panel, <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Lock</b> the surge hopper to prevent
                     more batch from being loaded.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ul id="ul_mcq_4mx_rcc" class="- topic/ul ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Click the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Lock/Unlock</uicontrol> button for the surge
                           hopper, at the bottom of the screen.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">The screen will prompt to either lock or unlock.</li>
                     </ul>
                     <note id="note_whj_dnx_rcc" class="- topic/note ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The picture shows the hopper locked.</p>
                     </note>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_kqg_5q1_tcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image7.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_r4x_5q1_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Go to the<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Melter JF</b> screen and select <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">JF Melter Energy</b> from the
                     dropdown menu.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ul id="ul_wd2_pnx_rcc" class="- topic/ul ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Verify the oxygen-gas ratio is<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> 2.30.</b>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">If the melter temperature is in manual, lower the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Gas Flow SP</b> in
                           increments of 1.34 Nm³/h (0.05 MSCFH) to keep the melter temperature
                           close to the operational temperature—but below 1371 °C (2500 °F).</li>
                     </ul>
                     <note id="note_cjm_tnx_rcc" class="- topic/note ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Minimum gas flow is 8.0 Nm³/h (0.30 MSCFH) for 1 MMBtu/h burners and 13.4
                           Nm³/h (0.50 MSCFH) for 2 MMBtu/h burners. </p>
                     </note>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_sc3_vnx_rcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image8.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_mkd_zq1_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <note id="note_r2x_q1w_rcc" class="- topic/note ">
                     <table id="table_zrb_s1w_rcc" class="- topic/table ">
                        <tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup ">
                           <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                           <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*" class="- topic/colspec "/>
                           <tbody class="- topic/tbody ">
                              <row class="- topic/row ">
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                    <p class="- topic/p ">
                                       <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">PPE Required:</b> Respirator or PAPR.</p>
                                 </entry>
                              </row>
                              <row class="- topic/row ">
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                    <p class="- topic/p ">Dust hazard.</p>
                                 </entry>
                              </row>
                              <row class="- topic/row ">
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                    <p class="- topic/p ">Toxic materials.</p>
                                 </entry>
                              </row>
                              <row class="- topic/row ">
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                    <p class="- topic/p ">Pinch hazard.</p>
                                 </entry>
                              </row>
                              <row class="- topic/row ">
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                    <p class="- topic/p ">Fall hazard. Utilize 3 points of contact on ladders. </p>
                                 </entry>
                              </row>
                              <row class="- topic/row ">
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry "/>
                                 <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                                    <p class="- topic/p ">
                                       <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">LO/TO</b>
                                    </p>
                                 </entry>
                              </row>
                           </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                     </table>
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Tools Required</b>: Rubber mallet, pry bar, vacuum, screwdriver, fire
                     blanket.</note>
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Perform the following tasks:</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ul id="ul_utb_w4x_rcc" class="- topic/ul ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Close the surge hopper gate.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">LO/TO</b> the charger. </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Disconnect the charger from the chopper.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Remove the retaining nut on the front left leg of the charger.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Remove the brakes from the rear wheels and pull the charger away from
                           the melter.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Cover the chopper opening using a fire blanket to prevent exhaust from
                           puffing out.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Slowly open the hopper gate.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Use a pry bar to break up batch buildup.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Push the charger back into position and secure it in place.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Remove the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">LO/TO</b>
                        </li>
                     </ul>
                     <note id="note_yxj_sqx_rcc" class="- topic/note ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Do not damage nearby instruments, such as the moisture analyzer.</p>
                     </note>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_aqt_lr1_tcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image9.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_jsk_nr1_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_c11_4r1_tcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image10.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_ggs_4r1_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">At the Zippe integration touch panel, unlock the surge hopper so that batch
                     can be loaded into the system.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ul id="ul_jxm_xqx_rcc" class="- topic/ul ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Click the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Lock/Unlock</uicontrol> button for the surge
                           hopper, at the bottom of the screen.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">The screen will prompt to either lock or unlock.</li>
                     </ul>
                     <note id="note_pkf_3t1_tcc" class="- topic/note ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The picture shows the hopper locked.</p>
                     </note>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_l2d_zqx_rcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image11.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_l3y_1s1_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">At the workstation, go to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Melter JF</b> screen and select <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">JF Melter
                        Energy</b> from the dropdown menu.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ul id="ul_mrh_mrx_rcc" class="- topic/ul ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Enter in the desired oxygen-gas ratio (typically 2.30).</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Begin increasing gas flow to maintain melter temperature above 1316 °C
                           (2400 °F).</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Click the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Apply to All Burners</uicontrol> button</li>
                     </ul>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_dl5_wrx_rcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image12.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_evj_gs1_tcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Restart the charger.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ul id="ul_wkc_kwx_rcc" class="- topic/ul ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Go to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Melter JF</b> screen and click the<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">
                              Overview</uicontrol> tab.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Click the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Charger Profile</uicontrol> button and check the
                              <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Allow</b> checkbox.</li>
                     </ul>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_ptp_xwx_rcc" class="- topic/fig ">
